1
00:00:01,700 --> 00:00:05,490
孩子们 圣诞节是一家团聚的日子
Kids, as you know, Christmas is a time you spend with your family.

2
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,320
在2006年的圣诞 我有三个选择
So in December of 2006, I had three options.

3
00:00:08,330 --> 00:00:11,150
和我妈妈还有 他的新男友克林特过圣诞
Spend it with my mom and her new boyfriend Clint,

4
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:14,720
也可以去找我爸爸 还有他的小甜心
spend it with my dad and his new girlfriend micro-brewing,

5
00:00:14,860 --> 00:00:16,930
或者乖乖待在斯塔藤岛
or head down to Staten Island to spend it

6
00:00:16,940 --> 00:00:20,130
和我那异常虔诚的堂姐斯坦西 还有她的家人一起度过
with my super religious cousin Stacy and her family.

7
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,270
但是以上三个选择我都放弃了
So I opted for none of the above

8
00:00:22,280 --> 00:00:26,190
决定在曼哈顿过2006年的圣诞
and decided to spend Christmas 2006 in Manhattan...

9
00:00:27,510 --> 00:00:29,410
和我的特殊家人一起过圣诞
celebrating with my other family.

10
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:35,090
我最后一场考试在 今天下午五点
Okay, I have one last paper due at 5:00 p.m. today,

11
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:37,550
在考试之前 我都要在图书馆里复习
so until then, I will be at the law library at school,

12
00:00:37,560 --> 00:00:39,240
没有任何事情可以改变我的计划
but I'm not to be disturbed for any reason.

13
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:41,230
老兄 睁开你的眼睛 你会摔到的
Dude, open your eyes. You're going to hurt yourself.

14
00:00:41,260 --> 00:00:44,320
不  不  对于我来说 平安夜所营造的冬日幻境
No, no. Christmas Eve winter wonderland is my reward

15
00:00:44,330 --> 00:00:45,930
就是对我胜利完成考试的奖励
for finishing my paper.

16
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:49,380
我闻到了浓浓的 肉桂曲奇的香味了  亲爱的
Baby, do I smell your Sinfully Cinnamon Cookies?

17
00:00:49,390 --> 00:00:50,510
没错
Yes.

18
00:00:50,580 --> 00:00:52,970
见鬼  我其他感官 的敏感度太高了
Damn me and my heightened other senses.

19
00:00:52,980 --> 00:00:54,340
一定很敏感
Must be strong.

20
00:00:54,350 --> 00:00:56,680
我出门了 我5点回来
Okay, I'll be back here at 5:00.

21
00:00:56,690 --> 00:00:59,870
给我留20块曲奇 记住不要把碗洗了
Save me at least 20 cookies and do not clean the bowl.

22
00:01:02,770 --> 00:01:04,060
这是个驯鹿!
Was that a reindeer?

23
00:01:04,070 --> 00:01:05,310
不要告诉我 (我要亲眼看)
I don't want to know!

24
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:12,780
我们原来的那个电话答录机
Hey, look. Our old answering machine.

25
00:01:12,790 --> 00:01:15,320
是啊 你从你走后 我们...我们就把它拆了
Oh, yeah. After you left, we, uh, we unplugged it

26
00:01:15,330 --> 00:01:18,630
这个容易让马修睹物思人 因为你以前经常用它
because it reminded Marshall of how you used to, you know, leave messages.

27
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:21,070
但是你们已经破镜重圆了
But hey, you guys are back together.

28
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:23,720
我建议我们把它装回去
I say we're plugging it back in.

29
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:26,890
算是你对回来的庆祝
It's good to have you back.

30
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:28,110
谢谢
Thanks.

31
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:31,090
里面还有些信息呢
Oh, hey, look, there's still some messages on here.

32
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:33,710
泰德 这是你老爹
Hey Ted, it's Dad calling to check in.

33
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:36,080
这个周末我要和克林特去钓鱼
I'm going fishing this weekend with my friend Clint,

34
00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:39,660
如果你留言给我的话 我下周回复你
so if I don't hear from you beforehand, I'll talk to you next week.

35
00:01:39,670 --> 00:01:41,420
是的 克林特 （泰德母亲的新男友)
Yes, same Clint.

36
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:45,620
马修 还在躺在沙发上 为莉莉的离开垂头丧气啊
Hey, Marshall. Are you lying on the couch right now moping about Lily?

37
00:01:45,740 --> 00:01:47,130
你在吗?不是这样的吗?
You are, aren't you?

38
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:49,440
不要再这样了 她不值得你这样...
Well, stop it. She's not worth it.

39
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:51,410
你应该忘记那个烂人
You gotta get over that Grinch.

40
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,920
事实上我没有说 烂人
But I didn't say "Grinch."

41
00:01:53,930 --> 00:01:55,740
我说了个更糟的词
I said a bad word.

42
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:58,230
非常非常糟的...
A very, very bad word.

43
00:01:59,390 --> 00:02:01,770
虚假
Oh, fudge.

44
00:02:01,780 --> 00:02:03,740
事实上我不是想说这是假的 (而是上帝啊)
But I didn't say fudge.

