49
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:22,020
我....什么?
I'm... a what?

50
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:24,670
我...是巴尼 这个是巴尼说的
I-- That was Barney, that was Barney.

51
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:26,470
- 泰德 不要说谎 - 是马修
- That was you, Ted. - That was Marshall.

52
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,600
马修给自己留言?
Marshall left a message for Marshall?

53
00:02:28,610 --> 00:02:33,410
这个也许是我 但是这个是很早以前的了
You know, it may have been me, but it was so long ago.

54
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:36,850
这个机器总把声音录的失真
Man, that machine, it really garbles your voice.

55
00:02:36,860 --> 00:02:38,180
所以听上去像是我说的 实际...
You know, it almost made it sound like I said...

56
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:40,100
你为什么叫我那个?
Why would you call me that?

57
00:02:40,110 --> 00:02:41,810
这个是个很难回答的问题
It was a fair question.

58
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:44,640
马修跟莉莉分手以后 他的情绪实在不好
Marshall's breakup with Lily had sent him into a deep depression

59
00:02:44,650 --> 00:02:46,270
没有什么可以帮他 走出失恋的痛苦
and nothing could get him out of it.

60
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,140
直到那天...
Until one day...

61
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,000
她太完美了
She was perfect.

62
00:02:50,730 --> 00:02:52,920
我失去了一个我梦寐以求的女人
I lost the perfect woman.

63
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:56,120
她给我机会时我该追上去的
I should have knocked her up when I had the chance.

64
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:57,900
够了
Okay. That's it.

65
00:02:58,390 --> 00:03:01,490
如果你还在继续神话她 那么你将永远都忘不了她
You're never going to get over her until you stop putting her on a pedestal.

66
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:05,460
告诉我一件莉莉做错的事情 要不就没有冰淇淋吃了
So no more ice cream until you tell me one thing that's wrong with Lily.

67
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,530
她只做过一件错事 (哇～只有一件错事的人多完美啊)
There's only one of her?

68
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:09,830
好吧
Okay.

69
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,220
她不跟你结婚了
She called off your wedding

70
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:13,840
弃你而去之后 你在旧金山沦为个油漆匠
and dumped you to be a painter in San Francisco.

71
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:15,250
你管她叫什么?
What do you call that?

72
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,510
自我独立?
Fiercely independent?

73
00:03:18,330 --> 00:03:19,660
勇气?
Brave?

74
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:24,140
我认为有点自私
I guess it was a little selfish.

75
00:03:24,150 --> 00:03:25,830
对了!
There you go.

76
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:30,550
在短时间内 星星之火  开始燎原了
And in almost no time, that spark turned into a roaring fire.

77
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:33,090
对 你是对的 莉莉会嘲笑身边所有事情
Yeah. No, you're right. Lily would laugh at anything.

78
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:34,790
她总是用一个很糟的理由 来表示她放弃了
She'd give it up for a bad pun.

79
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,820
我告诉你她的快乐神经有问题
I'm telling you, she's a laugh slut.

80
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:38,690
记得那次她大笑的事情吗?
Remember that time we heard her laughing

81
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,420
我们认为她在看 '老板度假去'
and we thought she was watching Weekend At Bernie's,

82
00:03:40,450 --> 00:03:43,480
结果她在看 '老板度假去2'
but it turned out she was watching Weekend At Bernie's 2?

83
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,180
她很有艺术细胞?
And her art?

84
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:47,180
我是莉莉 我是个艺术家
"I'm Lily, I'm an artist."

85
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:48,900
她甚至都没有得过奖
She doesn't even own a beret.

86
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:51,440
如果现实如她所说 她是个艺术家
Yeah, and if she's such a great "artist,"

87
00:03:51,450 --> 00:03:53,480
那她还玩pictionary? (pictionary 多人游戏 一人画图一人猜)
why does she suck at Pictionary?

88
00:03:53,490 --> 00:03:56,610
是谁把忍者之星画成了大卫之星? 是她吧?
Who draws a ninja star like a Star of David? Right, right?

89
00:03:56,620 --> 00:03:57,670
是啊!
Yeah!

90
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:59,860
- 再来庆祝下 - 好的
- Another round! - Yeah!

91
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:02,430
我是他哥们我当然要帮他啦
I was trying to help him. I'm his best friend.

92
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,290
这就是哥们改作的事情
That's the best friend's job.

93
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:07,680
是哥们就可以叫我那个?
The best friend's job is to call me that word?

94
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,240
是的
Yeah.

95
00:04:09,970 --> 00:04:11,490
天啊 泰德
Oh, Ted.

96
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,150
泰德你还没有长大啊
Oh, Teddy boy.

97
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:15,950
就一个单词的事情 有那么严重吗?
Why is this such a big deal? It's just a word.

98
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,980
每天我们都说无数的词
We use lots of words, every day.

99
00:04:17,990 --> 00:04:20,090
它和别的单词应该没有什么区别
It shouldn't be any different than any other word.

100
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,880
那你为什么现在不说?
Then why don't you say it now?

101
00:04:22,050 --> 00:04:23,470
烂人
Grinch.

102
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,260
你在算计我?
You timed that didn't you?

103
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:28,630
没错
Perfectly.

104
00:04:28,790 --> 00:04:30,720
至少你要道歉啊
Well, at least you apologized.

105
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,320
你道歉了吗?
You apologized, didn't you?

106
00:04:33,330 --> 00:04:34,430
当然
Oh, yeah.

107
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,960
我当时先说  对不起
"I'm sorry" were the first words out of my mouth.

108
00:04:36,970 --> 00:04:39,600
对不起 但是这不是道歉
I'm sorry, but I am not apologizing.

109
00:04:39,610 --> 00:04:41,710
我只是想帮他走出失恋
I was just trying to put the guy back together.

110
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,980
你把他的心撕碎了
You smashed him to pieces.

111
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:45,870
你就不能因为 一条留言跟我道个歉?
Are you seriously not going to apologize for leaving that message?

112
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:46,890
-不! - 为什么不?
- No! - Why not?

113
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:49,380
因为你今年夏天 的确是个烂人
Because, Lily, this summer, you were kind of a Grinch.

114
00:04:49,395 --> 00:04:50,910
- Oooh. - Oooh.

115
00:04:51,470 --> 00:04:54,780
你会后悔的 泰德・莫斯比
Oh, you'll be sorry, Ted Mosby.

116
00:04:55,740 --> 00:04:57,830
泰德・维维安・莫斯比
Ted Vivian Mosby!

117
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,110
我的全名可不是那样
That's not my middle name.

118
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:00,790
你用那种口气更你妈说话?

119
00:05:00,790 --> 00:05:02,840
好像你从来没有错过那个词一样
Like you've never said that word.

120
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,950
我又没有用那种口气 更你妈说过话
I don't kiss your mother with my mouth.

121
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:06,120
但是
Yet.

122
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:08,900
你病了?
Are you sick?

123
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:11,970
你是不是认为我缺乏性生活?
Is it sick to find maturity and experience sexy?

124
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:13,670
我是问  你是不是感冒了?
No, I meant do you have a cold?

125
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,980
我很好
I'm fine.

126
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:23,020
就是我的鼻子里有太多的东西了
I'm fine. My nose is just overflowing with awesome

127
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:24,670
我需要弄些出来
and I had to get some of it out.

128
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:27,870
如果你觉得有欠于我
Now, if you'll excuse me, the holidays are a time

129
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:30,070
假期真是让人孤独  无聊的时候
when people are lonely and desperate.

130
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,930
这是一年里最美好的时候
It's the most wonderful time of the year.

131
00:05:34,860 --> 00:05:37,740
我该去道歉吧 今天是平安夜
I should go apologize. It's Christmas Eve.

132
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:41,990
一个充满了砸门还有咒骂的平安夜?
Yeah. I mean, slamming doors and screaming curses?

133
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,560
如果我想要那些的话 我可以回家过
If I wanted that, I would have gone home for the holidays.

134
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:50,330
我没有看见槲寄生 但是...
I don't see any mistletoe, but...

135
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:54,400
神啊
Oh! Oh, God!

136
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:58,200
"保佑你" 我本可以做的更好...
Uh... "Bless you" would have been nice.

137
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:01,200
- 你病了 - 没有
- You're sick. - I'm not sick.

138
00:06:01,210 --> 00:06:02,810
- 你病了 - 你知道什么?我病了
- You're sick. - You know what? I am sick.

139
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:05,670
你说我病了我就病了!怎么可能?
Sick of you telling me I'm sick. What up?

140
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:16,300
爬了三层楼一滴也没有洒出来
Ahh... Three flights of stairs, not a drop spilled.

141
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,550
老兄
Hey, buddy.

142
00:06:18,820 --> 00:06:20,310
你确定这个管用?
You sure this is gonna work?

143
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,430
是的 这是我们的方式
Yeah, this is our thing.

144
00:06:21,470 --> 00:06:23,860
大学时  每当我想向她道歉 我就买杯啤酒给她
In college, whenever I wanted to make up with her, I'd buy her a beer.

145
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:25,550
-有意思吧? - 是的
- Cute, right? - Totally.

146
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,770
加上个免费的杯子
Plus free mug.

147
00:06:27,850 --> 00:06:29,610
起来吧
Okay, come on.

148
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:32,080
通常这招都有用
Usually that would've done the trick,

149
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:35,930
但这次的问题是 一杯啤酒不足以解决的
but it turned out this was a problem not even alcohol could solve.

150
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:45,460
事实上 啤酒确实有点用
Actually the beer helped a little.

151
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:51,810
她拿走了圣诞装饰
She took the decorations.

152
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:54,410
她拿走了圣诞装饰!
She took the decorations!

153
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:55,690
真是个烂人
What a Grinch!

154
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:57,710
这次我确实说了烂人这个词
That time I did say "Grinch."

155
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,730
好吧
All right.

156
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:00,550
我想我不得不给她打电话了
I guess I have to call her, right?

157
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:03,750
莉莉
Lily's cell phone.

158
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:05,920
她不是想听解释吗?
She'll listen to reason-- right?

159
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:08,850
你好 比利
Oh, hey, Billy.

160
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:11,910
事实上这很有趣 语音拨号拨到你那了
Actually, funny thing-- the voice dial got you.

161
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,180
我本打算打给...
I was trying to call...

162
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:16,250
天啊  很遗憾
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

163
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:20,160
假期对于每一个都是有点粗糙
Yeah, the holidays are a rough time for everyone, Billy.

164
00:07:21,090 --> 00:07:23,640
晚餐在下周三举行
Okay, yeah, dinner next Wednesday.

165
00:07:23,670 --> 00:07:25,090
好
Okay.

166
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:27,350
该死的语音拨号
Damn voice dial.

167
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:33,300
巴尼!你在那做什么?
Barney! What the hell are you doing?

168
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:36,450
进来 外面那么冷 你疯了吗?
Get in here, it's freezing outside. Are you insane?

169
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:41,180
要怪就怪莉莉的规矩 公寓里禁止吸烟
Hey, blame Lily and her oppressive "no cigars in the apartment rule."

